expr main (it's here nor there)

let message "Did you mean `it's neither here nor there`?"
let description "Corrects `it's here nor there` to the standard idiom `it's neither here nor there`."
let kind "Usage"
let becomes "it's neither here nor there"

test "All psychology but it's here nor there to me." "All psychology but it's neither here nor there to me."
test "Not that it's here nor there, but I also don't log short films or TV series." "Not that it's neither here nor there, but I also don't log short films or TV series."